# Component Patterns

## shadcn/ui First

Reach for shadcn primitives before writing raw HTML. If a primitive exists, use it:

```tsx
// ❌ raw div when Card exists
<div className="rounded-xl border p-6">...</div>

// ✅ shadcn Card
<Card><CardContent>...</CardContent></Card>
```

Common primitives available in this project: `Button`, `Card`, `Badge`, `Dialog`, `Sheet`, `Separator`, `Skeleton`, `Avatar`, `Tooltip`.

## Class Merging

Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional or merged classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

<div className={cn("base-class", isActive && "active-class", className)} />
```

## Tailwind v4 Tokens

Use theme tokens over arbitrary values for foundational surfaces:

```tsx
// ❌ arbitrary
<div className="bg-[#0a0a0a] text-[#ededed]" />

// ✅ tokens
<div className="bg-background text-foreground" />
```

Token reference: `bg-background`, `bg-card`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `text-primary`.

## Dark Mode

Dark mode is applied via the `.dark` class on `<html>`. Use `dark:` variants — do not check `prefers-color-scheme` in JS.

## Icons

Use Lucide icons at `h-4 w-4` (inline) or `h-5 w-5` (standalone). Import from `lucide-react`.

## Avatar Sizing

`Avatar` has no `size` prop. Control size with Tailwind:

```tsx
<Avatar className="h-12 w-12">...</Avatar>
```

## Suspense Boundaries for AI/Async Content

Wrap async Server Components that fetch or call AI APIs in `<Suspense>` with a `<Skeleton>` fallback:

```tsx
import { Suspense } from "react"
import { Skeleton } from "@/components/ui/skeleton"

<Suspense fallback={<Skeleton className="h-24 w-full" />}>
  <AISummarySection projectId={id} />
</Suspense>
```

Never block the page render waiting for an AI response — always suspend.

## Streaming Chat Status

When rendering chat messages, use the `status` field from `useChat` to show loading state instead of a separate `isLoading` boolean:

```tsx
const { messages, status } = useChat({ api: "/api/chat" })
const isStreaming = status === "streaming" || status === "submitted"
```

## Client Boundary Placement

Push `"use client"` as deep as possible. Pattern: Server Component renders the page shell and passes data down; only the interactive leaf (search input, chat widget) is a Client Component.

```tsx
// ✅ server fetches data, passes to thin client wrapper
// app/page.tsx (Server Component)
<ProjectSearchContainer initialProjects={projects} />

// components/sections/project-search-container.tsx
"use client"
// handles search state and renders results
```
